.*A*                                                                           
 
 
                        ID$CREATE
 
         ID$CREATE  creates the fonts used
    by ID to print blockletters. In order to create a font,
    one must define first the prameters of the font
    (e.g.) HEIGHT,WIDTH,FONT,WSN,ect.
    Then, one must define what the letters look like
    via the ASCII or OCTAL commands.
 
.*B*
         For more info on the prameters,see ID_HELP.
    For an example of font def, see ID$CREATE_ID.
.*X*
.*R*
.*K* OWNER
Rick Petkieiwcz, LADC
.*K* XINDEX
ID$CREATE.X
